IN

2009, NET WRITTEN PREMIUMS OF $889 MILLION WERE 5% LOWER THAN IN 2008. THE DECLINE WAS ATTRIBUTABLE TO BOTH THE NATIONAL PROGRAMS AND NORTHLAND BUSINESS UNITS, WHICH

EXPERIENCED CONTINUED NEGATIVE RENEWAL PREMIUM CHANGES THAT REFLECTED COMPETITIVE MARKET CONDITIONS AND THE IMPACT OF GENERAL ECONOMIC CONDITIONS, PRIMARILY ON THE COMMERCIAL TRUCKING, ENTERTAINMENT

