ECONOMIC ACTIVITY. NEW BUSINESS LEVELS IN 2009 WERE LOWER THAN IN 2008. IN INTERNATIONAL, BUSINESS RETENTION RATES IN 2009 DECLINED FROM 2008, PRIMARILY DUE TO UNDERWRITING ACTIONS TAKEN IN THE UNITED

KINGDOM, IRELAND AND AT THE COMPANY'S OPERATIONS AT LLOYD'S. RENEWAL PREMIUM CHANGES IMPROVED OVER 2008 AND NEW BUSINESS LEVELS DECLINED WHEN COMPARED WITH 2008.

