INTER-BANK LENDING RATE (CDI) FROM JANUARY 1, 2011 THROUGH THE CLOSING DATE OF THE TRANSACTION. AT DECEMBER 31, 2010, R$625 MILLION BRAZILIAN REAIS WAS EQUIVALENT TO

APPROXIMATELY $377 MILLION IN U.S. DOLLARS. THE PURCHASE PRICE IS EXPECTED TO BE PAID IN CASH FROM INTERNAL SOURCES IN THE FIRST HALF OF 2011. IN ORDER TO REDUCE ITS EXPOSURE TO A SIGNIFICANT

