THE

$2.00 BILLION DECLINE IN GROSS CLAIMS AND CLAIM ADJUSTMENT EXPENSE RESERVES SINCE DECEMBER 31, 2009 PRIMARILY REFLECTED THE IMPACT OF NET FAVORABLE PRIOR YEAR RESERVE

DEVELOPMENT AND PAYMENTS RELATED TO ASBESTOS AND ENVIRONMENTAL CLAIMS AS WELL AS OPERATIONS IN RUNOFF.

