GNMA, FNMA AND FHLMC (EXCLUDING FHA PROJECT LOANS) GUARANTEED RESIDENTIAL MORTGAGE-BACKED PASS-THROUGH SECURITIES CLASSIFIED AS AVAILABLE FOR SALE. ALSO INCLUDED IN THOSE TOTALS WERE RESIDENTIAL CMOS

CLASSIFIED AS AVAILABLE FOR SALE WITH A FAIR VALUE OF $2.07 BILLION AND $2.58 BILLION, RESPECTIVELY. APPROXIMATELY 38% AND 37% OF THE COMPANY'S CMO HOLDINGS WERE GUARANTEED BY OR FULLY COLLATERALIZED

BY SECURITIES ISSUED BY GNMA, FNMA OR FHLMC AT DECEMBER 31, 2010 AND 2009, RESPECTIVELY. THE AVERAGE CREDIT RATING OF ALL OF THE ABOVE SECURITIES WAS 'AA1' AT BOTH DECEMBER 31, 2010 AND

2009.

