DECEMBER 31, 2010 AND 2009, THE COMPANY HELD COMMERCIAL MORTGAGE-BACKED SECURITIES (CMBS, INCLUDING FHA PROJECT LOANS) OF $549 MILLION AND $714 MILLION,

