10. EARNINGS PER SHARE

BASIC EARNINGS PER SHARE WAS COMPUTED BY DIVIDING INCOME AVAILABLE TO COMMON SHAREHOLDERS BY THE WEIGHTED AVERAGE NUMBER OF COMMON SHARES OUTSTANDING DURING THE PERIOD. THE COMPUTATION

OF DILUTED EARNINGS PER SHARE REFLECTED THE EFFECT OF POTENTIALLY DILUTIVE SECURITIES.

ON

JANUARY 1, 2009, THE COMPANY ADOPTED THE UPDATED GUIDANCE RELATED TO EARNINGS PER SHARE AS DESCRIBED IN NOTE 1. THE IMPACT OF THE ADOPTION OF THIS GUIDANCE WAS A

REDUCTION OF PREVIOUSLY REPORTED BASIC AND DILUTED EARNINGS PER SHARE BY $0.03 PER SHARE AND $0.01 PER SHARE, RESPECTIVELY, FOR THE YEAR ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2008.

THE

FOLLOWING IS A RECONCILIATION OF THE INCOME AND SHARE DATA USED IN THE BASIC AND DILUTED EARNINGS PER SHARE COMPUTATIONS.

